summary: I honestly resent seeing Sansa hated on for being who she is. When I was younger, I loved stories of princesses and valiant...
question: I honestly resent seeing Sansa hated on for being who she is. When I was younger, I loved stories of princesses and valiant knights coming to the rescue. I had a dog named Lady I was close to, I daydreamt a lot about going away to some fancy kingdom, away from my boring home and both of us shaped our perspectives in a sense around what we learned from stories. I think those who judge her, refuse to see it from her perspective. Sansa's pov is actually quite common with young girls.
answer: Right???? She’s so normal in everything she does that they hate which isn’t shocking because people hate little girls. They don’t want to empathise with them or attempt to understand their subcultures. I’m extremely glad that we don’t have Sansa rejecting her younger self, she’s become jaded due to the horrific things she lived through but she never truly believes that she was once worthless. Any time she voices negative thoughts about herself it’s because she’s being abused. It’s not genuine or true.

summary: ↳ renly week 2018 + day three: renly/loras ‘if the smallfolk never cheer him on, renly's words always will; for every bit of...
caption:
↳ renly week 2018 + day three: renly/loras

‘if the smallfolk never cheer him on, renly’s words always will; for every bit of laughter at loras’s sake, renly will chuckle hushed praise against his throat; and for every dark bloom of blood loras beats beneath the flesh of those who doubt him, he will kiss another bloom, lovelier and deeper, into renly’s warm skin.

such a brave thing, the heart, to sit behind the ribs, to love and wait while cradled in a chalk-dust cage.

- the ribs of a broken umbrella, by @knight-of-the-flowers

body:
Yeah it’s very difficult how Robb and Rickon dead. Jon Snow has very difficult history with siblings.

But don’t you think his reaction about his real brother and Sister Aegon and Rhaenys. How they tortured and dead? Their killer Gregor Clegane is still alive and Jon was standing in front of him in Dragonpit. Can you imagine his reaction? When Dany tells him full story about them?
